Egg (
Figs. 1–3
).

Elongate-oval, yellowish-white (
Figs. 3
), deposited singly or quite often two eggs within the hole produced by female on the underside of host plant leaf (
Figs 1–3
). The only one egg was measured. Length of measured egg: 0.97 mm, width 0.42 mm.

